## Technical Content Requirements

### All Pages Must Include

| Element | Requirement |
|---------|-------------|
| H1 | Exactly one, containing primary keyword |
| Meta title | 50-60 characters, keyword-optimized |
| Meta description | 150-160 characters, include CTA intent |
| Canonical | Self-referencing |
| Hreflang | NL/EN alternate for bilingual pages |
| Schema markup | Page-type appropriate (FAQ, LocalBusiness, etc.) |

### Forbidden Patterns

- Keyword stuffing in headers
- Invisible text or hidden content
- Doorway page patterns (thin content redirecting to main page)
- Duplicate content across locations without unique sections
- External links to competitors
- Auto-generated content without human review

---

## Quality Checklist Per Page

Before marking any page complete, verify:

- [ ] Word count within specification
- [ ] H1 contains primary keyword naturally
- [ ] Required unique content section present
- [ ] FAQ section structured for schema markup
- [ ] Internal links preserved from legacy high-value pathways
- [ ] No template filler content remaining
- [ ] CTA present and actionable
- [ ] Mobile-scannable (short paragraphs, headers, bullets)
- [ ] Metadata optimized per Keyword Strategy
- [ ] Technical SEO elements correct

---

## Content Extraction Workflow

### Step 1: Identify Unique Content
From Firecrawl/WordPress extraction, mark:
- Location-specific information
- Genuine testimonials or reviews
- Unique FAQ questions
- Differentiating claims (verifiable)

### Step 2: Map to New Structure
Place extracted unique content into appropriate section per this specification.

### Step 3: Write Missing Sections
Create new unique content for required sections not covered by extraction.

### Step 4: Remove Filler
Delete all template text, generic descriptions, and repeated content.

### Step 5: Validate
Run quality checklist before marking complete.
